<worksheet >
    <title>TF-4 Laws of Sines and Cosines</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>Complete both parts to get M. Complete part a with progress on part b to get P.</p>
  </introduction>
  <page>
    <exercise workspace="2in">
      <introduction><p>A ship leaves a harbor and travels 45 miles due east. It then changes 
        course and travels 30 miles. From the ship's final position, a radar station back at 
        the harbor determines that the ship's current bearing from the harbor is 
        <m>\text{N } 55^\circ \text{ E}</m>.</p></introduction>
        <task><statement><p>Draw a diagram to model this situation.</p></statement></task>
        <task><statement><p>Find the possible bearing angles for the second leg of the ship's journey. Give a simplified 
          expression for your answer.</p></statement></task>
    </exercise>
  </page>
</worksheet>